    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available for acquisition is an investment-grade 2004 BMW M3 (E46) finished in Carbon Black. This example features the legendary S54 3.2L inline-six power plant, characterized by its individual throttle bodies and high-pressure Double VANOS variable valve timing, delivering a linear power band up to an 8,000 RPM redline. The drivetrain is anchored by a crisp Getrag 6-speed manual transmission and the M-Variable differential lock for optimal power delivery. This chassis has been meticulously preserved, with documented subframe reinforcement and rod bearing service already completed. Suspension geometry remains true to factory specifications with no bushing deflection, while the braking system utilizes cross-drilled rotors with excellent thermal dissipation. Every mechanical component, from the cooling system's expansion tank to the high-pressure oil lines, is in peak operational state, offering a visceral, analog driving experience that is increasingly rare.",
